cred Heart to Marguerite Marie Alacoque in the seventeenth century, through the French Revolution and its aftermath, to the construction of the monumental church that has loomed over Paris since the end of the nineteenth century. Jonas focuses on key moments in the development of the cult: the founding apparition, its invocation during the plague of Marseilles, its adaptation as a royalist symbol during the French Revolution, and its elevation to a central position in Catholic devotional and political life in the crisis surrounding the Franco-Prussian War. He draws on a wealth of archival sources to produce a learned yet accessible narrative that encompasses a remarkable sweep of French politics, history, architecture, and art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSacred Heart, Devotion toxHistory of doctrines. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  aarchitecture.  aart.  abasilica.  acathedrals.  acatholic church.  acatholicism.  achristianity.  adivine inspiration.  aeurope.  afamous places.  afrance.  afranco prussian war.  afrench catholicism.  afrench history.  afrench revolution.  ahistory.  alandmarks.  amarguerite marie alacoque.  amontmartre.  amonuments.  amysticism.  anational identity.  aparis.  aplague of marseilles.  apolitics.  areligion.  areligious vision.  aroyalist.  asacre coeur.  asacred heart.  atourism.  atourist destination.  awomen in history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052022136940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092401740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520924017423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520924017/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2